metadata.title: Biden keeps top scientist on staff despite “inappropriate behavior”

_source.body:
President Biden’s top science adviser has resigned after mistreating administration colleagues. Dr. Eric Lander submitted his resignation after the White House faced intense questioning about his employment. An internal review found that he bullied and disrespected staff, but the White House decided to keep him on the job — even though President Biden had laid out a zero-tolerance policy for such behavior. In his resignation letter, Lander said he never intended to cause hurt, and that it was his “fault “and his “responsibility.”

Brought to you by www.srnnews.com
